          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-06 08:32:07" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of the stem φαν- ‘to appear,’ {D:24.18}, {D:24.19}) pertaining to that which appears clear or evident</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>clear</Gloss>
                <Gloss>evident</Gloss>
                <Gloss>clearly</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In view of the contrast which exists in {S:04500202800026} between ἐν τῷ φανερῷ and ἐν τῷ κρυπτῷ, it is, of course, possible to translate ἐν τῷ φανερῷ as ‘that which is external’ and ἐν τῷ κρυπτῷ as ‘that which is internal,’ but it would seem better to preserve the contrast as ‘that which can be seen’ and ‘that which cannot be seen.’ See {D:24.29}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
